<plot>Fallen Moon is the story of Moto, a Japanese-born detective in the NYPD, a stern man who sees no shades of gray. Long estranged from his only family, his daughter, for her drug use and lifestyle, he spends his days picking up the pieces of victim's lives and his nights living his own half-life of lonely regret. When his daughter is brutally murdered on a lonely street, a chain of life-changing events are set in motion. Through a series of entwined story lines, Moto comes face-to-face with the world that stole his daughter from him, not as a cop but as a father. With the help of Ray MacKenzie, a man who knows too well the pain of losing a loved one, he meets April, his daughter's best friend, and discovers that beneath the layers and labels of criminals, prostitutes, and drugs, beats the hidden heart of humanity gone awry.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?188236</url></doc>
